page.title: 03ECOLOGY
page.content: In the{residential, industrial and {agricultural areas}within this sector are found clovers, poppies, daisies, buttercups, dandelions, nettles, grass, thistles, ivy, shepherds purse, chickweed, brambles, and groundsel. The most common{trees}are hawthorn and oak, along with horse chestnut, beech, plane and elderberry. The most common{insects}are ladybirds, flies, spiders, bees, butterflies, wasps and ants. Rabbits, bats, foxes and badgers, crows, robins, thrushes, blackbirds, swallows and most common {flora and fauna}can be seen. {Ponds and streams}contain frogs, pike, sticklebacks, tadpoles, dragonflies, water birds, water lilies, reeds, willows and watercress.
